Picante
Helps your phylogenies and relative ecology
Yinpeng Zhang
What is Picante?
Picante is a software package that
provides a comprehensive set of
tools for analyzing the
phylogenetic and trait diversity of
ecological communities.
Why Picante?
It allows to:
Manipulate phylogenetic and phenotypic
data;
Calculate phylogenetic diversity;
Analyze traits (matrix/community);
Analyze species/population interaction;
etc
Simple operation:
Basic R;
Combines other useful packages
(ggplot2, phylocom, ape, etc.);
What you can get?
What you can get?
PD: Faiths phylogenetic diversity (summing of all branch lengths within a
phylogeny)
MPD: mean pairwise phylogenetic distances
MNTD: mean nearest taxon distances
Taxonomic distinctness index
etc.
What you can get?
Tracking traits within taxa
Download: "install.packages(picante, dependencies=TRUE)
http://picante.r-forge.r-project.org/ http://cran.r-project.org/
